-- Greek IMF rep sees deal on austerity plan on Thursday
-- 
-- Thu Jun 23, 2011 10:39am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/23/us-greece-imf-representative-idUSTRE75M3Y120110623

 

 ATHENS  (Reuters) - Greece's representative to the International Monetary Fund said he expected a deal to be reached on Thursday between the Greek government and an EU-IMF delegation on the terms of an austerity plan. 

 "They are continuing the discussions they have to finalize the agreement on the expenditure cuts and some revenue issues," Panagiotis Roumeliotis told Reuters. Asked if he expected the talks to be successfully concluded on Thursday, he replied: "Yes, I think so." (Reporting by  Ingrid Melander ; writing by  Daniel Flynn )